FORM.AppraisalAddendumText: -:NEIGHBORHOOD BOUNDARIES:- The immediate neighborhood can be defined as: Chase Lane on the north; South Davis Blvd. on the east; Parkway Dr. in North Salt Lake on the south; Legacy Parkway on the west. The market area is the same as the neighborhood and is used for the statistics in the neighborhood section and the 1004MC form. -:NEIGHBORHOOD DESCRIPTION:- Homes in the neighborhood vary in age, style, construction quality, and overall appeal, but are compatible with one another. Schools, houses of worship and city parks are available nearby. Some convenience shopping is available nearby with major shopping and employment opportunities available ten miles to the south in Salt Lake City. There is a good road system in the area and access is convenient. -:ADDITIONAL FEATURES:- Additional features include a 11'x6' balcony, 3.5'x6' storage space on balcony, can lighting, oversized tub in the master bathroom, a walk-in closet in the master bedroom, a gas fireplace and vaulted ceilings in the kitchen and living area. -:COMMENTS ON SALES COMPARISON:- Due to the lack of Data in the market area none of the Comparable Sales bracket the subject in Sales Price, Adjusted Sales Price or GLA. Almost all Comparable Properties are located in the immediate condominium project. Comparable 4 is located over a mile away and has been added because it is outside the immediate project. All Comparable Sales, with the exception of Comparable 4, are similar in GLA, parking, recreational amenities and location and therefore there are minimal adjustments required. Each unit is addressed on a case by case basis below: Comparable sales 1, 2, 3 & 5 were all represented by the same listing agent, Ryan Hutchins. Through conversation it was disclosed that various motivations of the owner/seller within the previous year have encouraged a variety of asking prices and accepted offers. For this reason there are large discrepancies between sales prices and adjusted sales prices. There are no discernable differences in value contribution for location of each unit in the building between floor 1 and floor 3. Some of the Comparable Sales feature upgraded granite counters and have been adjusted based on the abundance or lack thereof, of granite used throughout the unit. Comp 1 is an older condo in the project and has been adjusted at $250 per year. Comp 1 is marginally inferior in condition due to typical wear and tear from habitation. Comp 1 features granite counter tops in the kitchen. Comp 2 is a year older than the subject but was not previously inhabited at the time of sale. Therefore the condition is considered to be the same as the subject. Comp 2 features granite counter tops in the kitchen. Comp 3 is an older condo in the project and has been adjusted at $250 per year. Comp 3 is marginally inferior in condition due to typical wear and tear from habitation. Comp 3 features granite counter tops in the kitchen. Comp 3 sold over six months ago but is used due to the lack of available data in the market area. Comp 4 is an older condo in a separate project and has been adjusted at $250 per year. Comp 4 is marginally inferior in condition due to typical wear and tear from habitation. Comp 4 features granite counter tops in the kitchen and bathrooms and plantation shutters. A paired sales analysis indicates a contributory value adjustment of $30 per square foot of GLA and an additional $4,000 per parking stall as compared to the subject because each parking space is in a guarded underground parking facility on location. Through market extraction Comp 4 has also been adjusted downward for the superior location, quality of construction and superior recreational options available to owners. North Salt Lake is a superior location because of surrounding habitations and proximity to local golf courses and Salt Lake City. This condominium project also offers a greater number of activities and facilities for their residents that include a spa, a pool, a salon, a clubhouse and a park. Comp 4 is superior in quality of construction because of materials used for interior finish and exterior ornamentation. Little weight is placed on this Comparable Sale because of the large differences overall and the fact that it is a community condominium project for persons over the age of 55. Comp 5 is current listing and has not previously been inhabited. Therefore the condition is considered to be the same as the subject. A conversation with the listing agent indicated that all construction materials and finish are the same as the subject and therefore no adjustments have been made for additional features. No comparable condo sales in this report have featured seller concessions therefore, there is no concessions adjustment made for Comp 5 nor is there an adjustment made for list to sales price ratio because Comp 5 is currently under contract. The final value is based on Comp 1 as it is the most recent sale, has a small number of adjustments and is located on the top floor like the subject. However, the final value has been rounded up to $149,000 due to the upward pull of the additional Comparable Sales. -:FINAL RECONCILIATION:- The value is based on the sales approach. The cost approach to value was not applicable because the subject is part of a larger project and cost to build is shared between many units. The income approach was not used due to lack of data. The scope of the appraisal includes the appraisal process except as noted. The intended client is shown herein. The purpose of the appraisal is to estimate the value for mortgage purposes.

MARKET.SalesConcessionDescription: The WFRMLS MLS indicates there were 17 closed sales during the past 12 months and 7 of those sales contained seller concessions which is 41% of the total transactions in this market area. Prior Months 7-12: 5 Sales; 2 with concessions; 40% of sales for this period. 4-6: 6 Sales; 4 with concessions; 67% of sales for this period. 0-3: 6 Sales; 1 with concessions; 17% of sales for this period. The concessions ranged between 1,300 and 5,313. The median concession amount is $4,620.
MARKET.NeighborhoodMarketabilityFactorsDescript: The WFRMLS MLS indicates there were 17 closed sales during the past 12 months and 3 of those sales were either foreclosures or short sales which is 18% of the total transactions in this market area. Prior Months 7-12: 5 Sales; 0 foreclosures or short sales; 0% of sales for this period. 4-6: 6 Sales; 3 foreclosures or short sales; 50% of sales for this period. 0-3: 6 Sales; 0 foreclosures or short sales; 0% of sales for this period.
MARKET.DataSourceDescription: The WFRMLS MLS was the data source used to complete the Market Conditions Addendum.
MARKET.MarketTrendsReconciliationComment: Effective Date: Thursday, August 28, 2014 Newly constructed condo type properties in the market area are inconsistent in nature due to demand and available land space. Therefore the inventory analysis indicates a mixed market. The number of sales for the current six month period has moderately increased as well as the number of listings. The median comparable sale price jumped around over the past year but overall is considered to be stable. The median comparable list price also jumped around but overall is considered stable because of varieties in quality of construction and location in the market area.. Most other indicators point to a stable market. This information, together with the appraiser's experience and knowledge, indicates a stable market.

No adverse site conditions or external factors were noted in the area that would adversely affect the subject property's value.

Additional features include a 11'x6' balcony, 3.5'x6' storage space on balcony, can lighting, oversized tub in the master bathroom, a walk-in closet in the master bedroom, a gas fireplace and vaulted ceilings in the kitchen and living area.
